			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2019</a> paper:</span><br><i>Operationalizing the integration of user interaction specifications in the synthesis of modeling editors</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/VascoSousa.html">Vasco Sousa</a>, <a href="../profile/EugeneSyriani.html">Eugene Syriani</a>, <a href="../profile/KhadyFall.html">Khady Fall</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1145/3357766.3359539">10.1145/3357766.3359539</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1c.html"><span class="tagM">T1C: Behavioural Semantics</span></a><ul><li> The paper primarily develops behavioural/executable semantics or ways to execute semantic definitions.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagL">T4A: Workbenches</span></a><ul><li> It includes substantial tool support or infrastructure relevant for engineering/using languages.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1d.html"><span class="tagL">T1D: Composition</span></a><ul><li> It emphasizes modularity/composition/integration (embedding or coordinating language components).
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5h.html"><span class="tagL">T5H: Usability</span></a><ul><li> It targets usability (developer interaction, comprehension, editing experience).
</li></ul></li></ul>
